What the governor's subordinates call "concentrated spam attack," others would probably call "active life stance."
In the Facebook era, it is easy to edit your image simply by blocking critics or erasing negative comments.
This is much less dusty than it used to be when it required sending people, collecting and burning critical front page newspapers, or arresting and shutting up protesters.
