Some protesters began throwing stones at the police station and the military base.
When the situation got tense, the soldiers were ordered by internal radio to "If the crowd resists more than three times, shoot them", as claimed in an official document that TIME reporters saw, but which was not published in the local media.
Jeremias Kayameh, the head of Koto Koto district in Anarotali, aged 50, felt threatened and called for calm by asking the crowd to go home.
