The reluctance to show diplomatic solidarity with us should remain on the conscience of those delegations.
"The most outrageous thing is that the failure of the Security Council to condemn the acts of terrorists encourages them to engage in further provocations and acts of terrorism, gives them a sense of impunity," said the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and added that "it would not be desirable for these barbarians to be convinced that someone in the Security Council is with them".
Vladimir Putin advocated limiting the number of unexpected business audits
Russian President Vladimir Putin, at an investment project meeting in the Far East, stated that the number of unplanned inspections of entrepreneurs should be reduced to 30 per cent of the number planned, and that the time limit for inspections should be limited to 10 days.
"Unscheduled inspections are generally carried out without appropriate coordination with the Public Prosecutor's Office; only 2-3 per cent are coordinated with the Public Prosecutor's Office, the rest being carried out on its own", quoted the President of TASS.
Vladimir Putin also said that investigators should not be allowed to seize servers and hard drives in businesses.
