"She interrupted his life to improve hers.
She didn't admit responsibility," she said.
"She hasn't shown remorse."
But Carter's lawyer said it was "a tragic case she deeply regrets."
However, Judge Lawrence Monis said that in his view, her "age, maturity or even mental illness did not have a noticeable effect on her actions".
