He decided to move to the position of Director of Production Coordination, said at the plant. Andrei Oklopkov had completed the task of providing a launch minimum for the first launch at the East launch site.
Mr. Oklopkov moved to work for CENI in 2013, with his service in space forces, particularly in Baikonur, and in Plesetska, in the North Space Station, he was the first deputy commander in the rank of colonel.
In 2009, Andrei Oklopkov became a criminal figure.
The investigation accused him of bribery: allegedly from his delivery, regional traders were paid for de-ordering but did not honour their obligations to clean the separate parts of the missiles in the Arkhangel region and the Republic of Komi.
In 2012, the jury found him not guilty.
Its technological development responsibilities in CENCI have been extended to various projects, but the main one has been the construction of a launch site in the Far East.
The then Federal Space Agency head, Oleg Ospenko, in an interview with JO, explicitly stated that the situation in the Eastern "was critical as early as October 2013".
The fact is that a strategic error was made in planning: the completion of the construction and the first launch of the Soyuz 2.1 launch vehicle were planned for the same time, at the end of 2015.
In order to make the launch by the end of the year, the construction was completed six months earlier and dates were shifted from December to July 2015.
In order to speed up the process, it had to be tricky: CENI specialists had begun to install technology equipment in a parallel way at facilities that had not been constructed.
The main supporter of this idea was Andrei Oklopkov.
Despite the risks and the transfer (instead of December 2015 the Soyuz did not fly until April 28, 2016), this idea has come true, says the source of the JO on space: "In other words, we would still not have made a single launch from the Eastern, but would have been building."
Vice-Premier Dmitri Rogozin, who is responsible for the creation of the launch site, called Andrei Oklopkov his "space Susan", a joke, but he was the one who almost always asked for information on the progress of the construction.
Mr. Oclopkov remembers his frankness: for example, in an interview with JO, he proposed that the Federal Agency for Special Construction (Spectro) be removed from its status as the only performer for the East and work directly with subcontractors: "Why do we have to put all the eggs in the same basket for the Special Struggle?"
This idea has found support in the government.
Since 2017, CENI has assumed the responsibility of a general contractor to complete the construction and construction work at the start-up and technical facilities scheduled for the fourth quarter.
According to JO, Mr. Oklopkov ' s transition to a new job was due to disagreement with the management of CENCI on the modalities for completing the construction of the space structures and complexes, as well as the methods of working with subcontracting organizations.
"It was decided that it would be best for everyone," says one of the top managers involved in the construction of East.
A government official, in turn, calls the decision odd: "He was one of the best professionals, finding him an equal replacement will not be easy."
